content:
Save Your Report in Salesforce Classic

Click Save to update an existing report with recent changes, or Save As to clone the original report without changing it. In Lightning Experience, click Clone to clone the report.

Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs)
Available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
Available in: Enhanced Folder Sharing

To create, edit, and delete reports:	
Enhanced Folder Sharing
Schedule Reports

Verify the name, description, and folder, then choose where to go next:
Click Save to save the report and go to the Reports home page
Click Save & Return to Report to save it and go back to the report run page.

To save your report at a specific role hierarchy level on sales, forecast, opportunity, and activity reports, select Save Hierarchy Level.

If you add a colon to your report name, it displays in two separate lines when you view the report. Use this information to categorize reports by name, or better display long names.
title: Saving and Cloning Reports in Salesforce Classic
